Outfit by @grytfitness

I have been doing Crossfit for 11 years.  It’s the one thing that I’ve been passionate about & it’s changed my life completely for the better.  Lately, I haven’t felt motivated to train.  I have been putting my energy into work and saving money that by the time I get off I’m to exhausted to train. 

I signed up for this competition with every intention to train for it, to find that passion again for the sport.  But I didn’t train like I had wanted to.  I wanted to withdraw from the competition because I wasn’t prepared for.  I felt embarrassed competing in the elite division, like I didn’t belong.  With my experience though, I wouldn’t feel right competing in a lower division, no matter where I’m at in my fitness journey. 

At the end of the day, I’m so so happy I put my self back out there, it felt amazing being on a competition floor again.  I went out there, had fun and just did the best I could.  I’m slowly starting to find that passion again. 🤗

Thank you @theirongames and volunteers for putting on this incredible event.  I got to meet new friends, see old ones & compete along side some bad ass babes. 

#crossfit #crossfitgirls #theirongames #compete #competition #fitness #fit #workout
